definition.value: Episodic ataxia type 2 (EA2) is the most frequent form of Hereditary episodic ataxia (EA; see this term) characterized by paroxysmal episodes of ataxia lasting hours, with interictal nystagmus and mildly progressive ataxia.

definition.value: Robinow syndrome (RS) is a rare genetic syndrome characterized by limb shortening and abnormalities of the head, face and external genitalia.
Unilateral renal hypoplasia is a form of renal hypoplasia (see this term), a renal developmental anomaly in which one kidney is small and has a deficit in the number of present nephrons.
Bilateral renal hypoplasia is a form of renal hypoplasia (see this term), a renal developmental anomaly in which both kidneys are small and have a deficit in the number of present nephrons.

definition.value: 17q11 microdeletion syndrome is a rare severe form of Neurofibromatosis type 1 (NF1; see this term) characterized by mild facial dysmorphism, developmental delay, intellectual disability, increased risk of malignancies and a large number of neurofibromas.
